frameDefinitions: A State_of_affairs has held and continues to hold up to the Reference_occasion.
This frame characterizes the likelihood that a Hypothetical_event will happen as a position on a scale of impossible to inevitable.
An Item is located on a Scale relative to a critical value which is determined by some Enabled_situation.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
LUs in this frame denote a period of time in which an Enabled_action becomes possible.
An Item is the only instance of its Type.
frameExamples: <t>To date</t>, the Department already has numerous requests for new systems to be developed.
It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
Allow a three-day <t>window</t> for delivery.  DNI
Steven is the <t>sole</t> survivor in his family.
listRoleDefinitions: A state which holds prior to and up through the <fen>Reference_occasion</fen>.
The time or event (normally speech time) with respect to which the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is located.
A numerical representation of the probability that a Hypothetical_event will occur.
A metaphorical representation of the position on the scale of likelihood that the Hypothetical_event will occur.
The event that is expected to happen with a certain likelihood.
The entity whose scalar property is specified.
The <fen>Scale</fen> is the attribute of the <fen>Item</fen> that is being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Enabled_situation</fen> by which the critical value is judged.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
The action that becomes possible through the existence of the period of time.
A quantity or other characterization of the period of the time in which an <fen>Enabled_action</fen> is allowed.  In this frame, the duration may be exact or inexact.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the one who performs the <fen>Enabled_action</fen>.
An <fen>Item</fen> is alone in its category.
<fen>Type</fen> specifies a category which in principle could apply to multiple items, but which is limited to the <fen>Item</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>How is your course going</fex> so far?
She was loving and concerned about others up to <fex>her dying breath</fex>.
There's a <fex>95 %</fex> chance of rain today.
Chances are <fex>slim</fex> that he'll pull through.
He's got a small chance <fex>of making it out alive</fex>.
It was <fex>hot</fex> enough to ignite the iron.
Can He make a rock too heavy <fex>for Him to lift</fex>?
<fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: at least from season to season
